Defendant Curtis M Hillmann in court, in custody, with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.   Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to all 3 cts of the amended information. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  victim/witness or the business or the employees

RESTITUTION:  $6278.34 to West Bend Mutual, $1715.28 to CGS Premier (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 as to each count (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD Surcharge:  $10.00 on each count

CONDITION TIME: 4 months jail, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

121 days credit if revoked.
